<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Very Comfortable  I stayed here for Christmas  New Year's Eve 2004. I found it a very pleasant and comfortable hotel. Mind you at that time it lacked a restaurant or bar but drinks and snacks may be purchased at reception and enjoyed either in your room or in the nice enclosed garden room. The staff was extremely pleasant and courteous.It located in a very safe part of town and there were always taxis parked out front to whisk you whereever you desired. The only problem I encountered was returning to the hotel from the western part of Berlin, many taxi drivers couldn't find it (mind you, my German is extremely poor) I later learnt that it might be helpful if you asked for specific directions (get them to write it down for you) from reception.All in all, it was a very comfortable above average budget hotel. 
